NAME: U7000
DESCRIPTION: U7000 refers to the ISL6258 or ISL6259 charging IC on Macbooks from 2008-2012

NAME: U7100
DESCRIPTION: U7100 refers to the ISL6259 or ISL9239 charging IC on Macbooks from 2013 to the present

NAME: CD3215
DESCRIPTION: This is a USB-C muxing chip responsible for USB-C communication with devices such as the laptop charger. The most common issue this chip is involved in is when a Macbook won’t charge or the charger is stuck at 5v instead of going to 20v.

NAME: U1950
DESCRIPTION: This chip often becomes corroded on pin 8 on the PP3V42_G3H pin causing PM_SLP_S4_L to go missing

NAME: U6100
DESCRIPTION: this is an SPI ROM chip that holds the BIOS which is necessary for the machine to POST or try and power on.

NAME: ISL6259
DESCRIPTION: This is a charging chip for Macbook motherboards from 2010 through 2015

NAME: U7501
DESCRIPTION: This chip is often responsible for creating PP3V3_S5,  PP3V3_S3,  PP3V3_S0,  PP5V_S5,  PP5V_S4,  PP5V_S0

NAME: U8900
DESCRIPTION: This chip creates the GPU power rails on the 820-3332 board to the 2012 and early 2013 15” Retina Macbook Pros. It becomes desoldered and is the cause of no video and kernel panics/crashes in that model most of the time.

NAME: U5110
DESCRIPTION: This chip is responsible for SMC_RESET_L in many Macbook models.

NAME: CD3217
DESCRIPTION: This is a USB-C muxing chip responsible for USB-C communication with devices such as the laptop charger. The most common issue this chip is involved in is when a Macbook won’t charge or the charger is stuck at 5v instead of going to 20v.

NAME: U7090
DESCRIPTION: This chip is often responsible for creating PP3V42_G3H

NAME: LP8550
DESCRIPTION: This is an LED driver responsible for creating the backlight on the LCD screen of Macbooks from 2011 through 2015

NAME: U7201
DESCRIPTION: U7201 is responsible for the 3.3v and 5v power rails on many devices.

NAME: U6903
DESCRIPTION: This chip is responsible for creating PP3V3_G3H in 2016-2018 model Macbook logic boards

NAME: U5701
DESCRIPTION: this is the keyboard controller chip that takes the keyboard and trackpad input and turns it into a USB device signal for the machine to process. If replacing a keyboard doesn’t fix an issue with keys not typing, check all traces between keyboard connector and this IC. This chip has programming so it must be replaced from a similar, ideally identical board.

NAME: U5000
DESCRIPTION: This is the System Management Controller(SMC) in macbooks from 2013-2015

NAME: U4900
DESCRIPTION: This is the System Management Controller(SMC) in older(pre-2013) macbooks

NAME: TPS51125
DESCRIPTION: This is a power chip responsible for the PP3V3_S5,  PP5V_S5,  and PP5V_S3 power rails on many A1278 model Macbooks

NAME: ISL9239
DESCRIPTION: This is a charging chip for Macbook motherboards from 2016-2018 responsible for charging the battery and creating the power rail PPBUS_G3H

NAME: ISL9240
DESCRIPTION: This is a charging chip for Macbook motherboards from 2018 through 2020

NAME: ISL6258
DESCRIPTION: This is a charging chip for Macbook motherboards from 2008 through 2009

NAME: TPS51980
DESCRIPTION: This is a power chip responsible for the PP3V3_S5,  PP5V_S5,  and PP5V_S3 power rails on many A1286 Macbook Pros,  A1297 Macbook Pros,  A1369 Macbook Airs,  A1466 Macbook Airs,  A1370 Macbook Airs,  and A1465 Macbook Airs

NAME: TPS62180
DESCRIPTION: This is a power chip responsible for many different power rails on 2016-2020 Macbook Pros,  most often known as the SSD buck converter chip responsible for NAND power rails

NAME: LP8545
DESCRIPTION: This is an LED driver responsible for creating the backlight on the LCD screen of Macbooks from 2011 through 2015

NAME: LP8548
DESCRIPTION: This is an LED driver responsible for creating the backlight on the LCD screen of Macbooks

NAME: CD3127
DESCRIPTION: This is a common typo,  the person typing CD3127 was most likely referring to a CD3217

NAME: CD3125
DESCRIPTION: This is a common typo,  the person typing CD3125 was most likely referring to CD3215

DESCRIPTION: This is a charging chip for Macbook motherboards from 2010 through 2015
